This paper deals with Bayesian optimal mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves allocation of resources to agents, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of randomness in optimization is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and economics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis of the benefits of randomness, which falls under information theory (cs.IT).
